    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>Flip Block is easy-to-use block to create interactive flip cards in WordPress. Showcase images, text, or other elements to encourage user interaction.</p>\n<p>Flip Block is perfect for displaying services, team members, or other information in a visually appealing manner.</p>\n<p>Flip Block comes with an intuitive interface and flexible customization options. You can control the width, height, and perspective of the flip cards, ensuring they fit seamlessly into your website&#8217;s design.</p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Choose one of the following options:\n<ul>\n<li>Go to Plugins <span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-exclude-emoji\">→</span> Add New in your WordPress dashboard, search for &#8220;Flip Block&#8221;, and click &#8220;Install&#8221;.</li>\n<li>Download the Flip Block plugin from WordPress.org, ensure the folder is zipped, and then upload it via Plugins <span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-exclude-emoji\">→</span> Add New <span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-exclude-emoji\">→</span> Upload.</li>\n<li>Open the block inserter within the Block Editor, search for &#8220;icon&#8221;, and the plugin should appear, allowing you to install it directly. Skip steps 2 and 3.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; screen in WordPress.</li>\n<li>Search for the block within the Block Editor and start using it.</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>0.1.3</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update: default block settings with support for older versions;</li>\n<li>Update: set different colors and backgrounds in flip sides as defaults;</li>\n<li>Update: set default spacing in flip sides;</li>\n<li>Update: prevent having not enough flip sides in flip block to avoid potential style issues;</li>\n<li>Update: improve navigation between flip block card and flip sides;</li>\n<li>Update: integrate new option to flip block, alowing to select flip side within block settings in editor sidebar;</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>0.1.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: overflow issue in Firefox;</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>0.1.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update: make Padding controls visible for Side block by default;</li>\n<li>Update: improve placeholder labels for Side blocks;</li>\n<li>Fix: width issue in block inserter;</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>0.1.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Release</li>\n</ul>\n"
    },
